<!-- ============================== HOW IT WORKS ============================== -->
<section class="section" id="how">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2 class="display h2">Two commands.<br/>One source of truth.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="steps reveal">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="n">01 · INSTALL</div>
        <h3>One SDK, your stack</h3>
        <p>Drop the SDK in. No scheduler wrapping. No per-job decorators. No changes to existing jobs.</p>
        <pre><span class="cmt"># pick your runtime</span>
<span class="ok">$</span> npm i @crontinel/node
<span class="ok">$</span> pip install crontinel
<span class="ok">$</span> go get github.com/crontinel/go
<span class="ok">$</span> gem install crontinel
<span class="ok">$</span> composer require crontinel/laravel
<span class="ok">$</span> dotnet add package Crontinel</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="n">02 · ROUTE ALERTS</div>
        <h3>Pick a channel</h3>
        <p>Slack, PagerDuty, email, webhook. HMAC-signed payloads. Quiet hours. Route once, in .env.</p>
        <pre><span class="cmt"># .env</span>
CRONTINEL_ALERT_CHANNEL=<span class="ok">slack</span>
CRONTINEL_SLACK_WEBHOOK=<span class="ok">...</span></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="n">03 · SLEEP</div>
        <h3>Listen instead of watch</h3>
        <p>We read scheduler events, worker state, queue internals and agent traces. When something drifts, you hear from us, not a user.</p>
        <pre><span class="cmt"># ci/cd deploy hook</span>
<span class="ok">$</span> crontinel check
<span class="ok">✓ 47 jobs · 3 workers · 2 queues · 4 agents</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

